<div class="l-constrained">

  <div class="home-buying-checklist-top">
    <div class="l-1col">
      <h1>Your home-buying costs checklist</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="home-buying-checklist__top-content">
      <div class="home-buying-checklist__top-content-text">
        <p>Buying a new home isn’t just about saving for a deposit and securing a mortgage. There are lots of other costs associated with buying a home that you might not have thought of, and they add up to thousands of pounds.</p>
        <p>This checklist lets you estimate how much it’ll cost you to buy your new home so you can put aside what you need to make your move as smooth as possible.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="home-buying-checklist__top-content-video">
        <iframe width="100%" height="200px" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/jfaZQBCzY44" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen title="Video: The total cost of buying a home"></iframe>
      </div>

      <div class="home-buying-checklist__collapsable">
        <p class="collapsable__trigger" data-dough-component="Collapsable" data-dough-collapsable-trigger="how-it-works">
          How to use this checklist
        </p>

        <div class="home-buying-checklist__collapsable-target collapsable__target" data-dough-collapsable-target="how-it-works">
          <p>We’ve listed each fee and put an average cost against it, based on a home price of £250,000. This gives you an idea of how much each charge will be.</p>
          <p>You can then type in the costs for your new property, check you’re not paying too much, and then our checklist will add it all together so you know how much you’ll need. You can also download the checklist or email it to yourself to use later or send to a partner or friend.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="l-1col">
      <h2>Work out your upfront costs before you buy your home</h2>
    </div>
  </div>

